$interpreted: Izumi: Ahaha, took a quick tour outside just now. Those monsters are nowhere to be seen~ Not a single trace left!
Izumi: I guess the Rayzor really wiped them all out~
Izumi: Wow, so these are the treasures the princess gave us? They are all sparkling and shiny~ So pretty.
Izumi: With these, we shouldn't have any trouble rebuilding our home~
Nigel: You're too noisy. Be quiet.
Izumi: However, even if the monsters are gone and we got the money, we still can't be at ease~
Nigel: What do you want to say?
Izumi: Not really~ I was just thinking to myself; there are no monsters here now and the Atlas void problem is solved as well.
Izumi: What's going to stop someone from wanting to occupy this place now?
Nigel: ......
Izumi: If some random country decides to show up here with their army...
Izumi: Poof! There goes all our hard work. All that monster clearing we did, our plans of rebuilding the home of the demihumans, gone, just like that~
Nigel: Just cut to the chase and tell me what you really want to say!
Izumi: Aww~ But I can't~ If sis Yamitsuki knows about this, I'm gonna be scolded by her again...
Nigel: SPEAK! Now!
Izumi: Atlas used to be just a port city. However, when the mining business began to bloom, it became a place where ability triumphed identity.

Izumi: That's how the more capable demihumans managed to secure a living here somehow.
Home of the demihumans?
If you really think about it, that title existed only because Kingdom of the Sun acquiesced it.
Nigel: ......
Izumi: Right now, we have the land and the money. The half-exposed Dragoneye Gem can also provide us with unlimited Soul Energy.
Izumi: With these advantages backing us up, we can create much more than just a simple "home"...
Nigel: What do you mean by that?
Izumi: A country.
Izumi: We can create a country that belongs only to the demihumans...
